<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="548" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-06-03"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 3, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 1st instant, and to thank you for the
                            accompanying copy of a letter which her Majesty’s secretary of state for
                            the colonies caused to be addressed to the under secretary of state for
                            foreign affairs, on being acquainted with the existence of the rumor
                            that an attempt was being made to fit out a privateer at Vancouver’s
                            island.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, your lordship’s obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F. W. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>